I currently have a level 4 rogue, I was 3 at the time. About a blue bulb from 4. Saw a decaying skeleton, normally wouldn't bother. This one had a staff though, and the corpse I was waiting to collect in QH had some bone chips on it too so I was like, why not? Could be a cracked staff, 1pp loot is obviously good at 3. I attack, get a shot in, here comes this monk and BAM, skeleton dead. I said &quot;excuse me&quot; and was given a &quot;your excused.&quot; So I sent a tell saying &quot;Did you not notice the mob was engaged or do you just KS like that usually?&quot; Yeah, it was a rude tell, but so is KSing. I didn't expect much more. Turned out to be the other person who suddenly makes a big deal. I get flamed for being a noob, though I had to explain having a new character and being a noob are 2 different things. Apparently only a noob would comment that they were KSed of a skellie like that.<br>
/shrug<br>
While I was running around going about my business, this person is standing there unable to do more than flame me. I was just amused by the whole thing. Person tells me about all their other high end characters and how I'm a noob, yet their reasoning behind KSing was &quot;cut me some slack, I'm a monk it had a stick that turned out to be a 2hb so I dropped it noob.&quot; Just sounded kinda silly to me.<br>
<br>
Oh well, hell of a long story for something so simple eh? KSing to me is KSing, regardless of the mob, unless someone didn't notice it was engaged, easy to do with lvl one mobs that can die so quickly. When it's out of pure greed because this person wanted a staff though, I think that's just plain wack. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/1/02 9:16:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=999.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/students/b/t/btk120/MOKONA.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Avarice is one of the seven.</span><hr size=1> Yeah, this idiot was being greedy.<br>
<br>
KSing happens.  Whether it's accidental (they were trying to help) or purposeful (they were trying to help and just hoping you'd die) it's a fact of life.  How you handle it is another story.<br>
<br>
If all this idiot can do is follow you around and tell high levels about you, or KS you back, /ignore him, then lead him through the Freeport sewers.  I've always appreciated the fact that they're not easily navigable, and the ones from West to East now have those zombie drowned citizens, who will make short work of him if he falls.<br>
<br>
(Yes, I know, someone came on and bitched about how someone did this with the Nektulos guards, but when it happens to you, you get cruel too.)<br>
<br>
My dad was playing his rogue and needed baking supplies.  He got yelled at for KSing a bat.  A BAT.  I laughed hard, insulted his intelligence, announced to the zone that I was putting him on ignore--it was a bat--and went about my merry way.  Most of them were already yelling at him to shut up.<br>
<br>
My Rallos experience decided it wanted to say something:<br>
<br>
Here, moron, have a plat for the staff and get back to your pharming druid on your carebear server, before I decide to loot it off your corpse.<br>
<br>
