<br>
What annoys me more are the ones who are KSing for loot and then, when informed that they were attempting to (or succeeded at) stealing your kill, claim they were &quot;just trying to help&quot;.<br>
<br>
I learned, early on on &quot;Orc Hill&quot; in the Greater Faydark, how to deal with these people.  I step back from the monster and let the monster aggro on them so they can take the damage from the monster they're trying to steal.  I've surprised and enraged a few people by doing that, but I don't feel it's my responsibility to stand there and take the damage so that someone else can steal the experience and the loot.<br>
<br>
When I am &quot;just trying to help&quot;, I toss around damage shields (Shield of Brambles) and the occasional damage over time spell (Stinging Swarm, which, it appears, don't have the effect of stealing kills like direct damage spells do), and  I'll heal someone who's in dire straits.<br>
<br>
Lasgalen, Initiate of Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubippinfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bippinfv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/2/02 2:01:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=999.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Avarice is one of the seven.</span><hr size=1> Two points:<br>
<br>
One is a question - easy to help with spells, but how to you help as a melee type. I see someone gets squashed by a mob - only way to help is engage the mob, maybe KS. Otherwise, the guy may die - dilemma. <br>
<br>
Another - advice. If the KSer say he just wanted to help - well, have him give you the loot then. You lost the exp. but the loot (staff? hehe) is still recoverable if the intentions were honorable. I would never keep the loot from any mob killed to help.<br>
<br>
My 2 cp's , maybe not even that much<br>
